						<div class="postbody">I guess it's very practical for gamers that doesn't need to bother about the settings for &quot;odd&quot; ROMs.. But I still think the options should be there. FCEUX is a pretty big source for my frustration. How do you develop something for VS-Zapper? The only way is that you start a VS-Zapper game, inject your own code (copy'n' paste to RAM), or hack your own ROM to match a CRC-value already in the VS-Zapper database. <br />I think Nintendulator behave in a similar way..</div>

					
