						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">natt wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">A real NES never has to guess what variety of mapper chip is on your particular board, or whether there's a resistor at R5.  It knows.</div><br />Wrong. The NES doesn't know shit, as far as it's concerned all carts have 32KB of PRG and 8KB of CHR! It's the cart itself that does all the magic, and since the cart (board, mapper, wiring, etc.) is missing from the emulator + ROM combination, the emulator has to get that information from somewhere in order to properly simulate the cart. Using the contents of the ROM to know what cart to simulate is a poor way of solving the problem, for the reasons oRBIT2002 mentioned.</div>

