						<div class="postbody">but we don't emulate &quot;the combination of the deck and the inserted cartridge&quot;, we emulate the deck and we try to handle the best we can what comes in the cart <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /><br /><br />this discussion is meaningful for me given that, even if in MESS we have a database of known good dumps, we also keep supporting iNES/iNES2.0/UNIF to allow homebrew software to run<br /><br />the problem is that either we establish some sort of 'central authority' which assigns in a meaningful way the mappers and keeps doing this until the firms in Taiwan and HK quit producing new carts, or there is no solution<br /><br />just look at the 5-6 known cases of mapper #s which have been assigned to 2 incompatible boards...</div>

